        {
          "id": "977d8fb861d3_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b2e5",
          "text": "I first wrote a new version of the Worldview dimension of the course in 2012, and in 2016 started to review the other dimensions. The ‘social design dimension’ initially authored by José Luis Escorihuela (Ulises) now has been editied with some new additions by Alyson Ewald and me. The ‘ecological design dimension’ was initially penned by Michael Shaw and now has been edited with new additions by Ezio Gori and me. I also re-wrote the ‘economic design dimension’ fundamentally on the basis of an early version by my friend Jonathan Dawson (now head of economics of transition at Schumacher College). So much had moved on in this exciting field since Jonathan’s 2008 version that many new aspects of economic design had to be included.",
